name: Trifrons
description:
This could be the 3 headed ogre from the recurring dream I had as a child, but it could also be a way to see the devil as in Dante Alighieri "Divine Comedy", or be an Asura...

Trifrons are also figure represented in pagan european culture, then on old churches. They were tolerated, then forbidden, then interpreted as contradictory meanings... 

Anyway, this form of figuration of a three headed character as a been a recurring thing in my art.

Aquatint etching.
